Dialogue: 69,0:00:01.78,0:00:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In the year 1732, during the Kyoho famine,\N many of the Hitogashima islanders died of starvation.
Dialogue: 69,0:00:08.57,0:00:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And on a day where the island was on the brink of death,\Na huge whale drifted ashore onto Omoto Beach.
Dialogue: 69,0:00:14.44,0:00:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The islanders rejoiced, gathering around to eat the whale,\N believing it to be a blessing bestowed from God.
Dialogue: 69,0:00:20.32,0:00:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A fisherman's daughter approached the whale, \Nand the whale's body glowed with a dazzling bright light.
Dialogue: 69,0:00:25.91,0:00:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The whale took the appearance of the girl in a flash.
Dialogue: 69,0:00:29.59,0:00:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It then proceeded to devour her.
Dialogue: 69,0:00:32.31,0:00:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The islanders, fearing divine punishment, \Ncame to worship the girl as the living goddess Hiruko.
Dialogue: 69,0:00:38.74,0:00:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the Hiruko legend that's passed down in Hitogashima.
Dialogue: 69,0:00:42.02,0:00:42.02,Default,chapter,0,0,0,,{OP}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.45,0:01:01.34,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}It's come to the point where I just want to hoard all your words
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.34,0:01:07.31,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}Even the ramblings from your travels are treasures to me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.31,0:01:10.49,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}Whether I sketch or erase it's all torn away
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.49,0:01:14.04,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}That's the price I pay for my awakening
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.04,0:01:19.60,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}Or my daydream's tricking me and I'm still lost in the unknown
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.60,0:01:22.77,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}Illuminated by the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.77,0:01:25.94,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}Your figure casts a shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.94,0:01:29.07,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}And when that silhouette wavers slightly
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.07,0:01:31.90,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}That happens to be my cue
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.78,0:01:38.87,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}I wish this were fiction but slow motion is how it begins
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.18,0:01:44.79,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}If the visceral warmth and traces you left behind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.79,0:01:50.96,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}Are protecting someone's future, I'll play the warrior
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.96,0:01:54.51,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}Amidst pain and sorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.51,0:01:57.51,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}I'll conquer my fears
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.51,0:02:00.56,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}It's a paradox of life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.56,0:02:03.02,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}Or perhaps God's algorithm
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.31,0:02:06.77,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}When our tactics overcome
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.77,0:02:11.53,OP,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(150,150)}We'll be laughing
