Dialogue: 69,0:02:16.31,0:02:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sense any Shadows?
Dialogue: 69,0:02:17.62,0:02:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:19.06,0:02:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Nagumo was right.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:20.99,0:02:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Karikiri isn't a Shadow.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:23.70,0:02:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:24.91,0:02:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, don't let yer guard down.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:26.73,0:02:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:28.18,0:02:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 69,0:02:30.19,0:02:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This heat never lets up, does it?
Dialogue: 69,0:02:32.29,0:02:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:33.05,0:02:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How about Tokyo?
Dialogue: 69,0:02:34.90,0:02:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it hotter than Wakayama?
Dialogue: 69,0:02:36.95,0:02:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not much different.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:39.44,0:02:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, have some cold barely tea.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:41.20,0:02:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:43.47,0:02:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Karikiri,
Dialogue: 69,0:02:45.49,0:02:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,weren't ya in Tokyo last year?
Dialogue: 69,0:02:47.94,0:02:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, ya told me ya went to a game event in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:52.73,0:02:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right! By the ocean in Makuhari!
Dialogue: 69,0:02:57.22,0:02:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Makuhari's in Chiba, though.
Dialogue: 69,0:02:59.18,0:03:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My, you're right! Tokyo sure was hot!
Dialogue: 69,0:03:02.46,0:03:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And my word, the crowds!
Dialogue: 69,0:03:05.70,0:03:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So ya like video games?
Dialogue: 69,0:03:07.84,0:03:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What do ya play?
Dialogue: 69,0:03:09.70,0:03:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I was all about RPGs in my younger days.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:12.41,0:03:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I play FPS games on PC.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:14.69,0:03:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I also like simulation games.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:16.97,0:03:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Are ya going back this year?
Dialogue: 69,0:03:18.90,0:03:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think I can this year.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:22.90,0:03:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But I really wanted to play Final Fantasy VII Remake.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:25.83,0:03:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When's it coming out?
Dialogue: 69,0:03:27.54,0:03:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Final Fantasy VII fun?
Dialogue: 69,0:03:29.96,0:03:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear that name a lot.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:31.33,0:03:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 69,0:03:32.25,0:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinpei, don't tell me ya ain't played it!
Dialogue: 69,0:03:35.06,0:03:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't born yet when it was out.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:38.04,0:03:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I really love the game's world.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:40.66,0:03:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe because it came out at the end of the century,
Dialogue: 69,0:03:43.56,0:03:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but the art and music have this very post-apocalyptic feel to them.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:47.12,0:03:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes ya think about how yer life will end.
Dialogue: 69,0:03:50.59,0:03:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Life, huh?
Dialogue: 69,0:03:52.86,0:03:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for ya, games are like how novels are for me?
Dialogue: 69,0:03:57.36,0:04:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Have ya heard of the novel \N{\i1}Swamp Man{\i0} by Nagumo Ryuunosuke?
Dialogue: 69,0:04:00.80,0:04:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I really like it.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:02.52,0:04:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately, I've been thinking that it's a story written about me.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:06.41,0:04:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That it's my story.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:08.31,0:04:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Swamp Man{\i0}?
Dialogue: 69,0:04:09.78,0:04:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know it, but I do know the Swampman thought experiment.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:15.25,0:04:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they similar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.03,0:04:27.75,signs,,0,0,0,,{=1}{\move(618,328,618,441.94,17,10695)\fscx132\fscy132\frz12.08\fax0.52\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\blur0.7}S{\fax0.542}w{\fax0.565}a{\fax0.588}m{\fax0.61}p {\fax0.655}M{\fax0.677}a{\fax0.7}n
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.03,0:04:27.75,signs,,0,0,0,,{=0}{\move(1356,451,1356,564.94,17,10695)\fscx82\fscy82\frz12.08\fax0.8\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\blur0.7}Nagumo \NRyuunosuke
Dialogue: 69,0:04:17.03,0:04:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:18.29,0:04:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, a copy of the protagonist appears and takes over their life.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:24.53,0:04:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No one realizes the switch,\Nnot even their friends or family.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:29.13,0:04:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The copy is a perfect reproduction of the protagonist's memories, personality, and DNA.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:34.96,0:04:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, y'could say the copy is the real thing.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:38.98,0:04:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What do ya think?
Dialogue: 69,0:04:40.77,0:04:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'd say they're the same.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:45.38,0:04:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Human cells are continuously being replaced due to metabolism.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:49.53,0:04:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Cell division creates countless copies.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:53.12,0:04:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The only difference is whether the replacement happens instantly or slowly over time.
Dialogue: 69,0:04:56.93,0:05:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the copy is the same as the original.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:00.50,0:05:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I think, yes.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:06.05,0:05:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Is yer head filled with thoughts like these?
Dialogue: 69,0:05:08.78,0:05:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya asked about the shadow sickness yesterday too.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:12.33,0:05:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned about the Hiruko legend too.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:15.46,0:05:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I was going to ask ya,
Dialogue: 69,0:05:18.43,0:05:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but Hizuru told me all about it.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:22.15,0:05:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,About 300 years ago, during the Edo period, a god washed ashore on this island.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:26.90,0:05:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Hiruko.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:28.85,0:05:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya could think of it as an ancient being from outside our world.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:33.61,0:05:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say, for example, it came from space.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:36.96,0:05:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A living being that was adrift in space.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:40.86,0:05:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps this creature copied and transformed into other things nearby, and sustained itself off the copied data.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:47.84,0:05:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are only so many things one can transform into in outer space.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:51.97,0:05:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So it most likely arrived on Earth in the form of a meteorite.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:56.69,0:05:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm guessing it fell into the ocean.
Dialogue: 69,0:05:58.75,0:06:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There are all sorts of things it could've copied there.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:03.40,0:06:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What follows is mostly from Hizuru's imagination.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:06.90,0:06:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But it matches up with the records we have of the Hiruko legend.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:11.85,0:06:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It transformed into a whale 300 years ago.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:15.98,0:06:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And, somehow, it washed ashore on this island.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:19.35,0:06:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers all gathered to look. \NOne of them, a fisherman's daughter.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:22.45,0:06:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It copied her.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:24.65,0:06:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where the shadow sickness began.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:27.67,0:06:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That is certainly how the Hiruko legend goes.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:30.74,0:06:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But ya can't be trying to say it's real, are ya?
Dialogue: 69,0:06:33.36,0:06:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:34.36,0:06:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shadows exist.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:37.44,0:06:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They killed Ushio.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:39.56,0:06:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They killed my parents.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:41.88,0:06:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're going to kill everyone who gathers for the festival here tomorrow.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:46.72,0:06:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my apologies.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:48.96,0:06:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Shinpei, ya must've read too many books.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:52.07,0:06:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that losing Ushio has upset ya.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:55.27,0:06:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps some rest is in order.
Dialogue: 69,0:06:57.54,0:06:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I already know everything.
Dialogue: 69,0:07:00.97,0:07:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Karikiri, ya know that this is the truth.
Dialogue: 69,0:07:04.74,0:07:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Because ya witnessed it all first-hand.
Dialogue: 69,0:07:10.41,0:07:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Whazzat? A whale?
Dialogue: 69,0:07:19.80,0:07:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't notice it at first,
Dialogue: 69,0:07:22.31,0:07:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but Dr. Hishigata showed it to me and said that it was ya.
Dialogue: 69,0:07:26.83,0:07:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And apparently the man on the left is his grandfather.
Dialogue: 69,0:07:31.41,0:07:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What are ya doing in a photograph taken over 70 years ago, Karikiri Masahito?
Dialogue: 69,0:07:37.35,0:07:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should I say Hishigata Shidehiko?
Dialogue: 69,0:07:40.38,0:07:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Shide!
Dialogue: 69,0:07:44.99,0:07:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Haine!
Dialogue: 69,0:07:48.94,0:07:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back here, Haine!
Dialogue: 69,0:07:51.00,0:07:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha—
Dialogue: 69,0:08:04.17,0:08:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Haine, hurry back now...
Dialogue: 69,0:08:08.01,0:08:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Shide!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.97,0:08:18.10,title,,0,0,0,,{\bord5\c&HC0A038&\blur7}Summer Time Rendering
Dialogue: 1,0:08:14.97,0:08:18.10,title,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}Summer Time Rendering
Dialogue: 69,0:08:20.52,0:08:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinpei—
Dialogue: 69,0:08:27.25,0:08:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move.
Dialogue: 69,0:08:28.48,0:08:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Move and I kill ya.
Dialogue: 69,0:08:30.13,0:08:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What did Dr. Hishigata say?
Dialogue: 69,0:08:33.16,0:08:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't answering your questions.
Dialogue: 69,0:08:35.13,0:08:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya answer mine!
Dialogue: 69,0:08:36.68,0:08:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the other photo.
Dialogue: 69,0:08:42.61,0:08:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Time passed, until 40 years ago.
Dialogue: 69,0:08:45.32,0:08:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when Dr. Hishigata's father took that photo.
Dialogue: 69,0:08:48.64,0:08:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya ain't a Shadow.
Dialogue: 69,0:08:50.42,0:08:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're no mere human, either.
Dialogue: 69,0:08:55.86,0:08:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Swamp Man, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.98,0:09:05.44,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(1055,742)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Fourth loop, July 23rd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NWhile investigating the old Hishigata Clinic
Dialogue: 69,0:09:02.98,0:09:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Hiruko? What would somethin' like that be doin' here?
Dialogue: 69,0:09:05.98,0:09:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No idea. It's just a guess.
Dialogue: 69,0:09:08.63,0:09:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But if this is Hiruko,
Dialogue: 69,0:09:10.97,0:09:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}then is there a connection between the Hishigata Clinic and the Hito Shrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.45,0:09:17.87,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(576,747)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Fifth loop, July 22nd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NFourth battery ruins, after Nagumo's and Nezu's pseudo loop
Dialogue: 69,0:09:14.94,0:09:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}The four-armed one might actually be Karikiri Masahito.
Dialogue: 69,0:09:18.39,0:09:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! That whippersnapper Karikiri?!
Dialogue: 69,0:09:20.87,0:09:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You two suspect this as well, don't you?
Dialogue: 69,0:09:23.08,0:09:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 69,0:09:24.50,0:09:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Haine...
Dialogue: 69,0:09:25.83,0:09:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If Hiruko is the mother of Shadows,
Dialogue: 69,0:09:27.85,0:09:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,then doesn't the Hito Shrine dedicated to her become really suspicious?
Dialogue: 69,0:09:30.71,0:09:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Karikiri is the head priest of the shrine.
Dialogue: 69,0:09:32.71,0:09:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but Karikiri is human, ain't he?
Dialogue: 69,0:09:35.60,0:09:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does the four-armed one hide its face?
Dialogue: 69,0:09:38.20,0:09:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's a Shadow, it could just transform into someone else.
Dialogue: 69,0:09:42.48,0:09:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if it's actually human and has no copy ability?
Dialogue: 69,0:09:46.58,0:09:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen it scan something.
Dialogue: 69,0:09:49.64,0:09:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But it did print.
Dialogue: 69,0:09:51.81,0:09:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the four-armed one is a human wearing the black mud that creates Shadows like armor?
Dialogue: 69,0:09:59.25,0:10:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's hiding its face, that means it doesn't want to be seen.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:03.36,0:10:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, it's someone we all know really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.71,0:10:07.71,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(78,104)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Sixth loop, July 22nd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NAfter canceling entry to Koba Mart
Dialogue: 69,0:10:11.54,0:10:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare they do that to Ryuunosuke.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:14.88,0:10:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The four-armed one must be Karikiri Masahito.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:17.94,0:10:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,After viewing our clash via your memories, I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:21.27,0:10:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How can ya know?!
Dialogue: 69,0:10:23.14,0:10:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That priest has always rubbed me the wrong way.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:27.07,0:10:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the four-armed one bothers me on a biological level, as well.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:30.19,0:10:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 69,0:10:31.36,0:10:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,His armor may hide his face, but it can't hide his humanity.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:35.43,0:10:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, the fact that Nezu couldn't pin his shadow means the chances he's human are extremely high.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:40.12,0:10:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But Karikiri should've been at the funeral then.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:44.15,0:10:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he left a Shadow in his place.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:46.58,0:10:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's really someone in there, an assassination could be effective.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:51.86,0:10:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Assuming he's human, killing him will be no problem.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:55.00,0:10:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I could go to the shrine, pretending to be there for a chat, and then {\i1}smash{\i0}.
Dialogue: 69,0:10:59.48,0:11:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's straight up murder!
Dialogue: 69,0:11:01.35,0:11:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We need more definitive proof.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:04.12,0:11:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's human, then he might be willing to negotiate if we can corner him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.56,0:11:11.07,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(1301,741)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Seventh loop, July 22nd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NAfter the battle at the gym
Dialogue: 69,0:11:08.88,0:11:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Shide received a burn on its left arm.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:11.52,0:11:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This will help us spot its true self.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.03,0:11:16.99,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(1301,741)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Seventh loop, July 22nd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NHishigata Clinic basement
Dialogue: 69,0:11:15.11,0:11:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at this.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:16.99,0:11:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Shide is Haine's guardian and the first child she ever gave birth to.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:21.06,0:11:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,His original name was Hishigata Shidehiko.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:23.64,0:11:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The founder of the Hishigata Clinic,\Nas well as its first director.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:27.95,0:11:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is this photo?
Dialogue: 69,0:11:31.10,0:11:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hishigatas have been in charge of religious services on this island since ancient times.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:35.69,0:11:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the Edo period, Shidehiko's father began pretending to be a doctor.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:40.22,0:11:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:41.72,0:11:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hishigata is Karikiri from the shrine, right?
Dialogue: 69,0:11:44.93,0:11:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hishigatas and Karikiris were originally from the same household.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:48.51,0:11:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Karikiris eventually split off from us and became independent.
Dialogue: 69,0:11:53.02,0:11:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you all know the legend of Hiruko?
Dialogue: 69,0:11:55.86,0:12:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The day Hiruko washed ashore, it became Haine,\Nand the islanders worshiped her as their god.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:02.75,0:12:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:04.24,0:12:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And eventually, Shidehiko produced a child with said god.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:09.21,0:12:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But not a Shadow created by scanning,\N birthed from outside the body.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:12.93,0:12:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This came from within. Haine's flesh and blood body was impregnated and she gave birth.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:17.93,0:12:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So he called himself the husband of a god and began calling himself by Haine's surname, Karikiri.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:22.64,0:12:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Shidehiko also had an older brother.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:25.76,0:12:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,After Haine gave birth, the Hishigata house split apart.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:28.39,0:12:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Karikiris became servants of God,\Nwhile the older brother became a family of doctors.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:33.32,0:12:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, Shide is a distant relative of ours?
Dialogue: 69,0:12:37.72,0:12:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 69,0:12:38.53,0:12:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And what of the child?
Dialogue: 69,0:12:41.46,0:12:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The child grew up and apparently was the spitting image of Shidehiko.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:46.66,0:12:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This must be the nature of Shadows.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:48.82,0:12:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The child Haine gave natural birth to was a clone of its father.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:53.86,0:12:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not the end.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:55.22,0:12:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing this, a certain ambition awoke within Shidehiko.
Dialogue: 69,0:12:59.18,0:13:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 69,0:13:00.55,0:13:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He made Haine copy his personality and memories, \Ntransferring them into the child.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:07.23,0:13:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus restoring his youth.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:11.69,0:13:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Disgusting.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:13.14,0:13:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder I never liked him.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:15.15,0:13:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My father delivered the baby.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:17.36,0:13:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He also took that photo.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:19.76,0:13:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,His current body is how he was born.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:23.05,0:13:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Shide has continued this secret rite and been reborn by Haine over and over.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:29.15,0:13:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's allowed him to live for 300 years.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:39.90,0:13:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a human-shadow hybrid!
Dialogue: 69,0:13:42.96,0:13:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good grief.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:44.05,0:13:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not fair that ya can loop, Shinpei.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:47.64,0:13:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,After only one day back, ya got this far.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:50.90,0:13:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But why don't ya sit down and have a drink?
Dialogue: 69,0:13:53.60,0:13:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't poisoned it.
Dialogue: 69,0:13:55.80,0:13:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So ya admit it?
Dialogue: 69,0:14:08.85,0:14:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then,
Dialogue: 69,0:14:10.57,0:14:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, when I was a mere 40 years old...
Dialogue: 69,0:14:13.10,0:14:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the summer of 1732.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:16.06,0:14:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The year of the Kyoho famine.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:19.65,0:14:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Have ya heard of it?
Dialogue: 69,0:14:21.00,0:14:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the Japanese history textbooks.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:23.93,0:14:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The harvests were terrible.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:25.71,0:14:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The adults who went fishing died too,\Nand we were left without the means to fish.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:30.45,0:14:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But then Haine appeared.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:33.14,0:14:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The people of this island have always believed that God resides in the things that wash ashore here,
Dialogue: 69,0:14:38.53,0:14:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so Haine truly was a god.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:41.46,0:14:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And apparently in exchange for feeding her humans,\Nshe blessed us with bounties of fish.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:45.63,0:14:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That part of the legend is incorrect.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:49.54,0:14:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All that happened was hundreds of islanders were turned into Shadows.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:53.12,0:14:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Shadows didn't need to be fishers,\Nso they were able to save the starving islanders.
Dialogue: 69,0:14:58.84,0:15:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitogashima survived thanks to me.
Dialogue: 69,0:15:01.93,0:15:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit screwin' around, ya bastard!
Dialogue: 69,0:15:03.56,0:15:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Y'think yer doin' the right thing?!
Dialogue: 69,0:15:06.22,0:15:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why did ya kill Shinpei's parents?!
Dialogue: 69,0:15:08.93,0:15:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they interfered, \Nmuch like ya did, Ushio.
Dialogue: 69,0:15:12.90,0:15:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They stumbled upon Hiruko cave and were about to announce it to the world.
Dialogue: 69,0:15:16.63,0:15:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of idiots, to be sure, \Nbut the mother was quite delicious.
Dialogue: 69,0:15:20.61,0:15:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Unforgivable piece of crap!
Dialogue: 69,0:15:22.89,0:15:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, would ya have been happier if I'd turned them into Shadows instead?
Dialogue: 69,0:15:39.62,0:15:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm not like ya!
Dialogue: 69,0:15:45.02,0:15:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna murder people,\Nand ya don't wanna die either, do ya?!
Dialogue: 69,0:15:50.93,0:15:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do ya protect Haine?
Dialogue: 69,0:15:53.55,0:15:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya can't accompany Haine on her way "home."
Dialogue: 69,0:15:58.96,0:16:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Give us Haine.
Dialogue: 69,0:16:00.80,0:16:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it can all be over, okay?
Dialogue: 69,0:16:03.36,0:16:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not my ending.\NIt's my duty to see my mother's wish fulfilled.
Dialogue: 69,0:16:09.82,0:16:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Damn it.
Dialogue: 69,0:16:11.21,0:16:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Damn it!
Dialogue: 69,0:16:12.74,0:16:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, ya never know.
Dialogue: 69,0:16:14.70,0:16:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My Shadow might exist.
Dialogue: 69,0:16:17.50,0:16:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Something's off!
Dialogue: 69,0:16:19.70,0:16:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull the trigger!
Dialogue: 69,0:16:21.11,0:16:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't sense any Shadows nearby!
Dialogue: 69,0:16:23.31,0:16:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why? Why is he...
Dialogue: 69,0:16:25.97,0:16:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot him, Shinpei!
Dialogue: 69,0:16:27.30,0:16:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our only chance to take out Shide!
Dialogue: 69,0:16:30.01,0:16:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand exactly what you're thinking right now.
Dialogue: 69,0:16:34.12,0:16:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why doesn't he have a burn on his left hand?"
Dialogue: 69,0:16:38.14,0:16:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct?
Dialogue: 69,0:16:40.17,0:16:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Shinpei, may I move now?
Dialogue: 69,0:16:44.46,0:16:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! I can't take this anymore!
Dialogue: 69,0:16:47.62,0:16:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ushio, wai—
Dialogue: 69,0:17:28.99,0:17:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 69,0:17:30.82,0:17:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it over now?
Dialogue: 69,0:17:33.28,0:17:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I'd do it.
Dialogue: 69,0:17:35.80,0:17:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want ya to have to do something like this.
Dialogue: 69,0:17:39.51,0:17:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I just couldn't let ya become a murderer.
Dialogue: 69,0:17:42.01,0:17:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 69,0:17:43.42,0:17:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna get my revenge.
Dialogue: 69,0:17:46.12,0:17:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yer too nice, Shinpei. \NIt would've eaten ya up inside.
Dialogue: 69,0:17:49.18,0:17:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya saw him as human, didn't ya?
Dialogue: 69,0:17:50.98,0:17:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Like how ya see me.
Dialogue: 69,0:17:55.20,0:17:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just leave all the dirty work to me!
Dialogue: 69,0:17:58.69,0:17:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ushio...
Dialogue: 69,0:18:02.97,0:18:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimme.
Dialogue: 69,0:18:06.14,0:18:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Y'all heard that?
Dialogue: 69,0:18:07.32,0:18:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I killed Shide.
Dialogue: 69,0:18:26.67,0:18:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin...
Dialogue: 69,0:18:31.18,0:18:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One down.
Dialogue: 69,0:18:36.96,0:18:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shide?
Dialogue: 69,0:18:38.04,0:18:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}H-How?!
Dialogue: 69,0:18:42.35,0:18:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, it can't be!
Dialogue: 69,0:18:44.76,0:18:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sorry, Shinpei!
Dialogue: 69,0:18:46.87,0:18:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Notice...
Dialogue: 69,0:19:01.22,0:19:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What a shame, Shinpei.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:05.90,0:19:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya needed to be just a little more objective.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:17.57,0:19:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're going alone?
Dialogue: 69,0:19:18.82,0:19:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ya want to convert him?!
Dialogue: 69,0:19:22.27,0:19:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm against this.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:23.49,0:19:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If Shide exposes his body, ya have to be able to pull the trigger without hesitation!
Dialogue: 69,0:19:29.54,0:19:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll kill him.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:30.55,0:19:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please wait!
Dialogue: 69,0:19:31.94,0:19:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Let me do this just once!
Dialogue: 69,0:19:36.36,0:19:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I just want to know what he's thinking.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:39.51,0:19:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or else, I can't kill him.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:43.33,0:19:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I want to hear why he killed my parents from his own mouth.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:49.29,0:19:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I just can't accept it otherwise.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:51.05,0:19:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But—
Dialogue: 69,0:19:51.55,0:19:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's important to me!
Dialogue: 69,0:19:53.23,0:19:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I wouldn't mind dying once more to find out.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:57.54,0:19:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll come with ya.
Dialogue: 69,0:19:59.74,0:20:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If the shrine is crawling with Shadows, \Nyou'll never even get to talk!
Dialogue: 69,0:20:05.73,0:20:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ushio is right.
Dialogue: 69,0:20:07.37,0:20:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you go alone, it's possible they'll make a move to capture you.
Dialogue: 69,0:20:14.65,0:20:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll accompany ya to the grounds.
Dialogue: 69,0:20:17.53,0:20:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay.
Dialogue: 69,0:20:18.73,0:20:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can we monitor the conversation too?
Dialogue: 69,0:20:22.91,0:20:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What if we put his phone in his breast pocket and have a group call going?
Dialogue: 69,0:20:25.74,0:20:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, can't hear a thing like that.
Dialogue: 69,0:20:29.00,0:20:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In that case, let's make gun shots our signal.
Dialogue: 69,0:20:34.25,0:20:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll shoot his Shadow first with two shots in order to confirm whether he's human or not.
Dialogue: 69,0:20:39.94,0:20:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If ya hear a third shot, that's yer signal to bust in!
Dialogue: 69,0:20:48.69,0:20:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How are ya feeling right now, Shinpei?
Dialogue: 69,0:20:51.24,0:20:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a child who's had his save data erased right before the final boss?
Dialogue: 69,0:20:56.17,0:20:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ushio is dead.
Dialogue: 69,0:21:01.87,0:21:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You little brats.
Dialogue: 69,0:21:04.98,0:21:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really think you could change my ending?
Dialogue: 69,0:21:08.59,0:21:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It'll be okay.
Dialogue: 69,0:21:09.86,0:21:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll be with ya, no matter what happens.
Dialogue: 69,0:21:13.04,0:21:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The only things you'll take back with you on your loop are despair and regret.
Dialogue: 69,0:21:18.29,0:21:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a pleasant journey!
Dialogue: 69,0:21:29.02,0:21:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinpei's whipped!
Dialogue: 69,0:21:31.55,0:21:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's like they're married!
Dialogue: 69,0:21:34.64,0:21:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 69,0:21:38.24,0:21:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Huh?
Dialogue: 69,0:21:40.03,0:21:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Ushio?
Dialogue: 69,0:21:42.17,0:21:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She was there just a second ago.
Dialogue: 69,0:21:48.76,0:21:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinpei?
Dialogue: 69,0:21:55.92,0:21:55.92,Default,chapter,0,0,0,,{ED}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.90,0:22:02.56,ED,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(200,200)}All traces of you vanished into the sea breeze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.56,0:22:07.56,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H6173A3&\3c&H22C3F8&\blur5\fad(200,200)}But even now I still see visions of you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.64,0:22:15.34,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HC3A644&\3c&HE9EBBB&\blur5\fad(200,200)}In reality I only have vivid memories
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.34,0:22:16.76,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HC3A644&\3c&HE9EBBB&\blur5\fad(200,0)}To play in my head over and over again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.76,0:22:20.27,ED,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H9AFAF8&\blur5\fad(0,200)}To play in my head over and over again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.57,0:22:25.67,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H6989A1&\3c&H73E97B&\blur5\fad(200,200)}Even if it's all just a lie
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.67,0:22:29.79,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H6989A1&\3c&H73E97B&\blur5\fad(200,200)}Please be close by my side
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.09,0:22:32.85,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H6A70EE&\3c&H83EF82&\blur5\fad(200,200)}Right next to me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.25,0:22:38.60,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HE5D78D&\3c&HE4F4FB&\blur5\fad(200,200)}I fell for you before too long
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.60,0:22:41.68,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HE5D78D&\3c&HE4F4FB&\blur5\fad(200,0)}But time alone was what progressed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.68,0:22:42.46,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H59A599&\3c&HF8EAC3&\blur5\fad(0,200)}But time alone was what progressed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.97,0:22:46.95,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H59A599&\3c&HF8EAC3&\blur5\fad(0,200)}I wanna go back
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.25,0:22:55.94,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB67647&\3c&HD0C1AC&\blur5\fad(200,200)}I've listened to my share of heartbreak songs
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.73,0:23:03.74,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB67647&\3c&HD0C1AC&\blur5\fad(200,200)}Spending my days torn up and crying but now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.74,0:23:06.29,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB67647&\3c&HD0C1AC&\blur5\fad(200,200)}I want to move on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.89,0:23:09.62,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB67647&\3c&HD0C1AC&\blur5\fad(200,0)}I shouldn't act tough and just finally be
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.62,0:23:11.26,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HEBCEAB&\3c&HF4F3E8&\blur5\fad(0,200)}I shouldn't act tough and just finally be
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.54,0:23:14.54,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HEBCEAB&\3c&HF4F3E8&\blur5\fad(0,200)}True to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.67,0:23:17.96,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HC16C32&\3c&HBFC385&\blur5\fad(200,0)}But it's too late for that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.96,0:23:20.58,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB4D1F0&\3c&HEAEEFD&\blur5\fad(0,200)}But it's too late for that
